  "text": "Additionally, we investigate the case of negative bribery, a variant introduced by Faliszewski et al. [CITATION_1] , where it is not allowed to pay voters to vote for the preferred candidate, both for the unweighted and weighted versions. We obtain that the unweighted negative bribery problem is likewise solvable in polynomial time for almost all variants considered so far, except for SM combined with C EQUAL where it is N P-complete, and for SM combined with C DIST , which still is unsolved, like its correspondent in the positive version. The weighted negative version is N P-complete for all variants considered so far. Our results are summarized in Table 2 in Section 4.",
